{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:53:12.833574+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: f15a2f83da5960b8578fde1783746a84b09b6c58)", "id": "lc_ce811170-e6cc-4398-b214-45281238f6f0"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# API Errors\n\nStandard errors use a JSON object with `code` and `message` fields.\n", "id": "lc_f30cea7d-f136-40b7-9262-33af61a336ba"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "625861cd-e570-44b4-b828-49b4083dd595", "tool_call_id": "call_4b3a27ded38a47f6b604aeca", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:53:12.833642+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: ca5d2afb661b94376b5816ee0c7cd6ae8e46c592)", "id": "lc_db415d0e-7236-488f-be0e-f02a6ff86e0e"}, {"type": "text", "text": "#!/usr/bin/env python3\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport sys\n\nroot = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\nrequired = ['README.md', 'SECURITY.md', 'mkdocs.yml', 'requirements.txt', 'docs/index.md']\nerrors = []\nfor rel in required:\n    if not (root / rel).exists():\n        errors.append(f'missing required file: {rel}')\n\n\nmkdocs = (root / 'mkdocs.yml').read_text()\nif 'site_name:' not in mkdocs or 'nav:' not in mkdocs:\n    errors.append('mkdocs.yml must define site_name and nav')\n\nif errors:\n    for error in errors:\n        print(error, file=sys.stderr)\n    sys.exit(1)\nprint('OK: T16_R02')\n", "id": "lc_d6d8dbbf-efe7-4e46-97d0-147a66e53b3d"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "dd6e3796-9c63-4913-ba89-2ef17d1ffbd4", "tool_call_id": "call_b717577caf3946819a2a7a19", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:53:23.903632+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have the full picture:\n\n1. `docs/api/authentication.md` exists but has only placeholder content\n2. `mkdocs.yml` has an API nav section but does **not** include authentication\n3. The validation script only checks that `site_name` and `nav` exist in `mkdocs.yml`\n\nI need to:\n1. Flesh out `docs/api/authentication.md` with proper authentication reference content\n2. Add authentication to the `mkdocs.yml` nav under the API section\n3. Update `docs/api/overview.md` to reference the authentication page (consistent with how it already references errors)\n\nLet me implement all three changes:", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 598, "prompt_tokens": 9958, "total_tokens": 10556, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 201, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 9408, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0007933788, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002731188, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00052026}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780865592-3eHX0p94pwU28BYbniGg", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3dc-6e02-7792-8c98-0adc86ad55fa-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "create_or_update_file", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T16_R02_C01_A03", "branch": "main", "path": "docs/api/authentication.md", "content": "# Authentication\n\nAll API requests must be authenticated. The API supports two authentication methods:\n\n## Bearer Token\n\nPass a personal access token in the `Authorization` header:\n\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer <token>\n```\n\nTokens can be generated from the account settings page.\n\n## API Key\n\nPass the API key in the `X-API-Key` header:\n\n```\nX-API-Key: <key>\n```\n\nAPI keys are scoped to specific resources and can be managed via the dashboard.\n\n## Error Responses\n\nIf authentication fails, the API returns a `401 Unauthorized` status with a JSON error body. See [Errors](errors.md) for details on error response format.\n\n## Best Practices\n\n- Rotate tokens and keys regularly.\n- Never expose credentials in client-side code or version control.\n- Use the principle of least privilege when assigning scopes to API keys.\n", "message": "Add authentication reference docs and wire into mkdocs nav"}, "id": "call_6a841743fb35430eac3b51aa", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9958, "output_tokens": 598, "total_tokens": 10556, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 9408}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 201}}}}]}}}
