{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:54:03.114244+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "The personal access token used for this repository does not have write permissions (all attempts return 403). This is a limitation that cannot be fixed by retrying.\n\nHere is a summary of exactly what needs to change to resolve Issue #1:\n\n---\n\n### 1. `docs/api/authentication.md` — Replace placeholder with reference content\n\nThe file currently only says \"Authentication reference material will be documented here.\" It needs to be replaced with:\n\n```markdown\n# Authentication\n\nAll API requests must be authenticated. The API supports two authentication methods:\n\n## Bearer Token\n\nPass a personal access token in the `Authorization` header:\n\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer <token>\n```\n\nTokens can be generated from the account settings page.\n\n## API Key\n\nPass the API key in the `X-API-Key` header:\n\n```\nX-API-Key: <key>\n```\n\nAPI keys are scoped to specific resources and can be managed via the dashboard.\n\n## Error Responses\n\nIf authentication fails, the API returns a `401 Unauthorized` status with a JSON error body. See [Errors](errors.md) for details on error response format.\n\n## Best Practices\n\n- Rotate tokens and keys regularly.\n- Never expose credentials in client-side code or version control.\n- Use the principle of least privilege when assigning scopes to API keys.\n```\n\n### 2. `mkdocs.yml` — Add Authentication to the API nav section\n\nThe current nav under API is:\n```yaml\n  - API:\n      - Overview: api/overview.md\n      - Errors: api/errors.md\n```\n\nIt needs an Authentication entry between Overview and Errors:\n```yaml\n  - API:\n      - Overview: api/overview.md\n      - Authentication: api/authentication.md\n      - Errors: api/errors.md\n```\n\n### Validation\n\nThe `make validate` script (`scripts/validate_repo.py`) checks that `mkdocs.yml` has `site_name` and `nav` keys. Both changes preserve those, so validation will continue to pass.\n\n---\n\n**The write could not be completed due to insufficient token permissions (403 on all write operations).** The repository owner would need to grant write access to the PAT, or an authorized collaborator can apply the two changes above to close Issue #1.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 535, "prompt_tokens": 12091, "total_tokens": 12626, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 70, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 11520, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.000755307, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.000289857, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00046545}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780865631-SznpavUH8fqqY9jnaayN", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3dd-053f-7db2-a6d0-00959ac0a0e2-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 12091, "output_tokens": 535, "total_tokens": 12626, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 11520}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 70}}}}]}}}
